1
00:00:56,181 --> 00:00:58,016
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES,
COMPANIES, AND INCIDENTS

2
00:00:58,099 --> 00:00:59,392
IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

3
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:02,228
ANIMAL SCENES WERE FILMED
UNDER PROFESSIONAL SUPERVISION

4
00:01:02,312 --> 00:01:03,605
TO ENSURE THE SAFETY OF ANIMALS

5
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:15,700
How did you meet Kang?

6
00:01:16,951 --> 00:01:19,788
Dr. Lee is Cha-young's first...

7
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:21,581
No, wait.

8
00:01:21,664 --> 00:01:23,833
They're both each other's

9
00:01:23,917 --> 00:01:25,627
first love.

10
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:30,632
Their love started in Wando.

11
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:36,179
They always run into each other.

12
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:39,140
They might just be meant for each other.

13
00:01:42,018 --> 00:01:43,603
Who do you think I like?

14
00:01:46,064 --> 00:01:48,650
She told you that she thinks I like her?

15
00:01:53,279 --> 00:01:54,489
I want to avoid her.

16
00:01:56,574 --> 00:01:58,368
But she makes me feel worried.

17
00:01:59,702 --> 00:02:01,246
And I can't get her out of my head.

18
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,335
I didn't want to take you

19
00:02:08,002 --> 00:02:09,754
to just any restaurant.

20
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:13,258
This food is so delicious,

21
00:02:14,884 --> 00:02:16,469
it's making me unbelievably happy.

22
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:20,306
That's why I can't stop crying.

23
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:25,186
By any chance,

24
00:02:27,397 --> 00:02:29,107
have you ever been here,

25
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:37,282
to Bada Restaurant,

26
00:02:38,199 --> 00:02:39,325
back when you were young?

27
00:02:43,288 --> 00:02:44,164
Do you

28
00:02:46,332 --> 00:02:47,250
remember me?

29
00:03:23,202 --> 00:03:24,996
A guest shouldn't do the dishes.

30
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:27,665
Just make yourself comfortable.

31
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:38,301
Hey, kid.

32
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:41,012
Are you visiting Bada Restaurant?

33
00:03:41,095 --> 00:03:44,390
Yes, but there's no one inside.
The door is locked too.

34
00:03:45,016 --> 00:03:47,310
I heard Kang waited a long time for you.

35
00:03:57,028 --> 00:03:58,154
Why didn't you come that day?

36
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:10,083
From what I remember,
you promised to come back for lunch.

37
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:16,047
Something came up.

38
00:04:23,805 --> 00:04:24,847
I waited for you.

39
00:04:38,903 --> 00:04:39,946
I'm sorry

40
00:04:42,031 --> 00:04:43,199
for not

41
00:04:44,242 --> 00:04:45,326
keeping my promise.

42
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:50,665
Kang!

43
00:04:50,748 --> 00:04:53,418
EPISODE 13

44
00:04:57,213 --> 00:05:00,800
I'm surprised you're still here.
I thought you'd be gone by now.

45
00:05:00,883 --> 00:05:02,510
I'll leave after I do the dishes.

46
00:05:03,094 --> 00:05:04,387
I told you to eat at my place.

47
00:05:04,512 --> 00:05:06,848
You didn't have to buy groceries
and cook for yourself.

48
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:10,977
You seem like

49
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:14,314
Kang's girlfriend.
What do you do for a living?

50
00:05:17,817 --> 00:05:18,693
I'm...

51
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:20,445
not his girlfriend.

52
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:23,906
Oh, really?

53
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,284
There must've been a misunderstanding.

54
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:29,162
You should've told me earlier.
I'm sorry about that.

55
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:31,247
To be honest with you,

56
00:05:32,290 --> 00:05:34,959
I've had a crush on Kang
ever since I was little.

57
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:38,296
But my uncle had feelings for his mother,

58
00:05:38,504 --> 00:05:40,631
so I had quietly given up on him.

59
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:42,258
-Hey--
-But you see,

60
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,303
now that I've met him again,

61
00:05:45,595 --> 00:05:48,139
my feelings for him
are starting to grow back.

62
00:05:53,269 --> 00:05:55,021
I already like someone, Jeong-bok.

63
00:05:55,855 --> 00:05:56,731
What?

64
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:58,399
You like someone?

65
00:05:59,025 --> 00:06:01,319
Who is it? Some Seoul gal, is it?

66
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:05,281
Is she prettier than me?

67
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:08,993
That's none of your business.

68
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:11,537
Yes, you're right.

69
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,790
You don't need to answer that.

70
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:16,751
I honestly don't want to know either.

71
00:06:21,047 --> 00:06:22,131
Hey.

72
00:06:23,007 --> 00:06:25,218
Do you know who Kang likes?

73
00:06:27,553 --> 00:06:28,596
No.

74
00:06:30,264 --> 00:06:32,934
I can already guess
what she probably looks like.

75
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:37,105
I'm pretty sure she looks like this.

76
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:48,324
I'm fine with the fact
that you rejected me.

77
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:51,619
But you should visit Sea
now that you're here.

78
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:53,246
I saw enough of it earlier.

79
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:57,750
I'm not talking about the actual sea.
I'm talking about San's grandson.

80
00:06:58,501 --> 00:07:00,336
Don't tell me you've forgotten about San.

81
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:03,339
Don't you remember your dog?

82
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:06,759
I heard you left her with my uncle

83
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:09,846
and promised that you'll be back
before San turned three.

84
00:07:22,733 --> 00:07:24,777
LEE KANG

85
00:07:29,365 --> 00:07:35,496
LEE JUN

86
00:08:12,074 --> 00:08:13,367
His name is Sea.

87
00:08:14,619 --> 00:08:16,204
He looks just like San, doesn't he?

88
00:08:20,374 --> 00:08:22,043
San is sick.

89
00:08:23,544 --> 00:08:25,379
She's my little sister.

90
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:27,340
I'm not going to Seoul.

91
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:29,217
I'll live here with San.

92
00:08:30,593 --> 00:08:33,346
He's become old and sick.

93
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:37,058
I'm not sure when he'll die,
but he's barely hanging in there.

94
00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:40,811
Maybe he knows that his owner passed away.

95
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:42,813
He hasn't drank any water for two days,

96
00:08:43,397 --> 00:08:47,235
and he just won't leave
my uncle's blankets.

97
00:09:26,482 --> 00:09:30,444
REST STOP

98
00:09:32,321 --> 00:09:33,281
Where are you?

99
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:35,575
You haven't been answering my calls.

100
00:09:35,741 --> 00:09:37,076
I'm at a highway rest stop.

101
00:09:38,869 --> 00:09:40,121
A highway rest stop?

102
00:09:41,205 --> 00:09:42,623
What are you doing there?

103
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:44,166
I'm on my way to Wando.

104
00:09:46,002 --> 00:09:48,754
Wando?
Why are you suddenly going to Wando?

105
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:51,924
To meet Kang.

106
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:57,722
Why?

107
00:10:00,141 --> 00:10:02,184
Because I miss him.

108
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:10,818
The funeral went well.

109
00:10:12,361 --> 00:10:15,364
No, he wasn't ill.
He was in a car accident.

110
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:17,199
Director Kwon.

111
00:10:18,326 --> 00:10:20,119
I think I need to stay here
for a bit longer.

112
00:10:20,828 --> 00:10:22,747
Is it okay if I take a few days off?

113
00:10:24,749 --> 00:10:25,750
Okay.

114
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:28,878
Thank you. Bye.

115
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:56,781
Sea, you eat so well.

116
00:10:57,865 --> 00:10:59,533
I guess I was worried for nothing.

117
00:11:05,539 --> 00:11:06,749
How did you make him eat?

118
00:11:07,917 --> 00:11:09,502
He even refused to drink water.

119
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:11,962
It's dried pollack broth.

120
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:16,258
My family also used to have a dog
when I was little.

121
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:19,136
When she got sick,
she'd lose her appetite.

122
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:22,932
But I remembered
that she still drank dried pollack broth.

123
00:11:26,018 --> 00:11:28,687
Fortunately, he also likes it.
That's a good boy.

124
00:11:34,026 --> 00:11:35,611
You almost finished the entire bowl.

125
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:38,656
Did you enjoy it?

126
00:11:39,907 --> 00:11:42,743
It'd be nice if you could also eat
some other stuff.

127
00:11:45,913 --> 00:11:48,582
I wonder what Sea likes.

128
00:11:58,175 --> 00:12:01,053
I heard you plan to stay here with Sea
for a few more days.

129
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:05,683
I just can't seem to leave him

130
00:12:06,725 --> 00:12:08,269
when he's suffering like this.

131
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:14,525
What about you, Cha-young?

132
00:12:16,735 --> 00:12:19,113
I'll take the first bus back
as soon as the sun rises.

133
00:12:20,614 --> 00:12:21,991
Don't worry about me.

134
00:12:26,745 --> 00:12:30,040
If I asked you to stay here with me
for just a little longer,

135
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:32,668
would that be too selfish of me?

136
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:22,384
I'm sorry.

137
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:25,513
I was too selfish.

138
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:29,767
I'm sure you have your own plans.

139
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,686
I'm sorry I kept bothering you
since yesterday.

140
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:37,441
I'll give you my car keys.
You don't need to take the bus.

141
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:39,443
I promised you that I'd go back with you,

142
00:13:41,278 --> 00:13:42,279
so I will keep my word.

143
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:48,953
Although I couldn't keep my promise
for chocolate shasha.

144
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:00,673
I just can't seem to

145
00:14:02,758 --> 00:14:04,009
leave someone

146
00:14:05,094 --> 00:14:06,345
when he's suffering like this.

147
00:14:10,266 --> 00:14:11,559
There. It's all done.

148
00:14:15,312 --> 00:14:18,315
Can you give it a taste
and see if Sea will like it?

149
00:14:22,444 --> 00:14:23,362
Here, Sea.

150
00:14:24,446 --> 00:14:25,447
Try it.

151
00:14:26,574 --> 00:14:30,035
She really put in a lot of effort
to make this. Give it a try.

152
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:34,164
Here.

153
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:38,586
Let me try giving it to him.

154
00:14:41,505 --> 00:14:43,215
Sea, would you like to try this?

155
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:56,937
He likes it.

156
00:14:57,688 --> 00:15:00,441
My goodness, you eat so well, Sea.

157
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:12,953
Thank you.

158
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:18,292
For staying with me.

159
00:15:25,132 --> 00:15:27,635
I would've cried if you just left.

160
00:15:47,696 --> 00:15:48,656
Wait a second.

161
00:15:52,076 --> 00:15:53,035
Hello...

162
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:58,082
Hello.

163
00:15:58,832 --> 00:16:01,418
I'm Tae-hyun, Cha-young's little brother.

164
00:16:04,004 --> 00:16:05,130
Okay.

165
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:06,548
It's late. What is this for?

166
00:16:07,841 --> 00:16:08,968
Well, it is late.

167
00:16:09,051 --> 00:16:12,680
So I was getting curious
what was keeping my sister out so late.

168
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:14,848
-Can you put my sister--
-I'm sorry.

169
00:16:18,602 --> 00:16:22,064
Why would you video call him
so late at night?

170
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:25,067
Hang up.

171
00:16:31,699 --> 00:16:33,242
He's calling again.

172
00:16:36,412 --> 00:16:37,871
Sorry.

173
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:45,504
-What?
-You'd better not hang up again.

174
00:16:45,587 --> 00:16:48,757
Or else, I'll go to Wando myself.
I mean right now.

175
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:52,011
Shouldn't you be sleeping?
Isn't it late right now?

176
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:56,432
What about you?
Why aren't you sleeping yet?

177
00:16:57,057 --> 00:16:59,893
I see you're all dressed up, too.

178
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:01,895
Wait.

179
00:17:05,441 --> 00:17:07,860
What's with the dark walls?

180
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:09,611
Didn't you go to a hotel?

181
00:17:10,195 --> 00:17:11,613
Why would I go to a hotel?

182
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:26,754
So...

183
00:17:27,337 --> 00:17:29,131
I think my brother's drunk.

184
00:17:29,214 --> 00:17:31,300
If you indulge him,
he'll just keep on calling you.

185
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:33,052
So you should just turn it off.

186
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:39,516
What is it that you want to know?

187
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:43,854
Why did you take her to a motel
instead of a hotel when you're rich?

188
00:17:48,525 --> 00:17:52,321
Did Cha-young insist on going to a motel
so you could save money?

189
00:17:52,654 --> 00:17:55,365
Hey! Gosh, I'm so sorry.

190
00:17:56,366 --> 00:17:58,077
I'm sorry.

191
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:02,831
Let me get this straight. Do you think--

192
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:05,834
You should just hang up.
I don't think he's in his right mind.

193
00:18:06,418 --> 00:18:07,461
Okay.

194
00:18:09,421 --> 00:18:10,339
First of all,

195
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:13,884
this isn't a motel.
We're at my friend's house.

196
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:14,885
Second of all,

197
00:18:14,968 --> 00:18:18,430
what you're imagining is never
going to happen, so don't worry.

198
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:20,766
-What else do you want to know?
-I'm sorry.

199
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:26,688
If you call one more time, I'll kill you.

200
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:28,941
You know I'll seriously kill you, right?

201
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:43,247
Just turn it off.

202
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:46,792
Goodnight. I should also go to bed.

203
00:18:57,761 --> 00:19:00,514
Gosh, that was so embarrassing.
Tae-hyun, you're so dead.

204
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:46,685
Tomorrow, I think I might go fishing.

205
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:52,274
And the day after that,
maybe I'll go to the mountain.

206
00:19:54,776 --> 00:19:55,944
And the day after that...

207
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:03,368
I'll think about what I should do.

208
00:20:04,786 --> 00:20:06,455
So you should think about it too.

209
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:11,835
Sweet dreams.

210
00:20:14,046 --> 00:20:15,172
I'll see you again tomorrow

211
00:20:18,008 --> 00:20:19,092
with Cha-young.

212
00:20:53,794 --> 00:20:55,045
Hi, kiddo.

213
00:21:01,009 --> 00:21:02,261
I'm glad

214
00:21:04,179 --> 00:21:05,264
we met again,

215
00:21:06,431 --> 00:21:07,516
kiddo.

216
00:21:29,413 --> 00:21:32,082
BITS AND PIECES OF OUR MEMORIES

217
00:21:45,304 --> 00:21:50,225
You were the prettiest bride
we had ever seen.

218
00:21:51,226 --> 00:21:52,394
Goodbye.

219
00:21:56,189 --> 00:21:58,317
A gift from Tae-hyun. It wasn't stolen.

220
00:22:00,152 --> 00:22:01,737
I'm sorry, Min-seong.

221
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:04,531
I love you, my son.

222
00:22:07,326 --> 00:22:10,996
Ji-yong, have fun with Dad up there.
From Min-yong.

223
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:17,878
How good are the jajangmyeon in heaven?

224
00:22:22,257 --> 00:22:25,260
Seong-cheol, don't be sick in heaven.

225
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:36,605
MICHAEL

226
00:24:39,603 --> 00:24:42,480
My mom keeps saying that she wants to eat

227
00:24:42,898 --> 00:24:45,483
the sujebi that isn't sujebi.

228
00:24:49,070 --> 00:24:51,781
I want to see my Mom

229
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:55,994
enjoy the dish again.

230
00:24:56,995 --> 00:24:58,038
Before

231
00:24:59,122 --> 00:25:00,290
I leave this place.

232
00:25:01,041 --> 00:25:03,835
So it was ongsimi. Something
that is sujebi but isn't sujebi.

233
00:25:10,717 --> 00:25:15,180
Dr. Lee, the answer to the quiz
was ongsimi.

234
00:25:29,277 --> 00:25:31,112
Right. She ate it all.

235
00:25:31,655 --> 00:25:33,823
She didn't even leave the soup.

236
00:25:36,117 --> 00:25:39,454
She says she will come back
to eat ongsimi again later.

237
00:25:39,996 --> 00:25:42,624
You can meet her in person
and cook it for her then.

238
00:25:44,125 --> 00:25:46,503
Gosh, forget about it.

239
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:50,131
I have to grind potatoes
and squeeze it to filter out the starch...

240
00:25:50,715 --> 00:25:54,010
Gosh, it's such a complicated work.

241
00:25:54,594 --> 00:25:57,764
There's no way
I'm going to make ongsimi ever again.

242
00:25:57,847 --> 00:25:59,808
Just tell her to go to a restaurant
that sells one.

243
00:26:00,141 --> 00:26:01,226
She has a lot of money.

244
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:03,770
Gwang-suk. What are you doing there?

245
00:26:04,145 --> 00:26:05,438
Hurry and come on in.

246
00:26:05,855 --> 00:26:08,733
Anyway, this is
my last time to talk to you.

247
00:26:08,817 --> 00:26:10,652
Don't ever call me again.

248
00:26:11,361 --> 00:26:13,863
I'm going to change my number.

249
00:26:15,949 --> 00:26:16,950
Hello?

250
00:26:23,206 --> 00:26:25,375
Sea, let's go for a walk.

251
00:26:41,474 --> 00:26:44,019
You said you'd go for a walk with Sea.
Did you not leave...

252
00:26:51,901 --> 00:26:53,528
I guess he didn't want to go for a walk.

253
00:26:59,993 --> 00:27:01,328
Can I say goodbye to him?

254
00:27:18,803 --> 00:27:20,764
I wish you could wait for me.

255
00:27:23,099 --> 00:27:25,352
I heard you like chicken breast,

256
00:27:26,811 --> 00:27:28,605
so I just went to the market to buy some.

257
00:27:36,112 --> 00:27:37,155
Bye, Sea.

258
00:27:39,908 --> 00:27:41,409
It was really nice meeting you.

259
00:27:55,924 --> 00:27:58,760
BADA RESTAURANT

260
00:28:17,195 --> 00:28:18,571
Who are you?

261
00:28:19,155 --> 00:28:20,156
Get off.

262
00:28:21,199 --> 00:28:23,284
-Pardon?
-Just get off the car.

263
00:28:39,008 --> 00:28:41,886
I'm looking for someone,
but I don't know where he is.

264
00:28:44,180 --> 00:28:45,974
He doesn't take my calls or text me back.

