Oh, no.

533
00:53:25,535 --> 00:53:27,913
I'm sorry. I dropped the shrimp.

534
00:53:28,538 --> 00:53:30,081
My shrimp...

535
00:53:31,041 --> 00:53:33,126
WHO'S THAT GUY?

536
00:53:33,209 --> 00:53:34,669
Gosh, you scared me.

537
00:53:34,753 --> 00:53:36,922
IS HE REALLY HER BOYFRIEND?

538
00:53:37,005 --> 00:53:38,924
WHO IS HE? HUI-NA, TELL US WHO HE IS

539
00:53:39,007 --> 00:53:41,384
-Hello.
-Hello.

540
00:53:41,468 --> 00:53:42,302
Hello.

541
00:53:42,385 --> 00:53:43,845
IS HE A SURPRISE GUEST?

542
00:53:43,929 --> 00:53:45,555
He's a surprise guest.

543
00:53:45,639 --> 00:53:46,640
DO THE HEART DANCE AGAIN

544
00:53:46,723 --> 00:53:48,266
Bang, bang.

545
00:54:04,366 --> 00:54:05,825
Do you think it's possible

546
00:54:06,743 --> 00:54:08,828
to climb a mountain on one leg?

547
00:54:11,915 --> 00:54:13,583
I'm going to try.

548
00:54:15,085 --> 00:54:16,753
I'll climb the mountain in front of me

549
00:54:17,879 --> 00:54:19,047
on just one leg.

550
00:54:24,844 --> 00:54:26,513
I think Dr. Lee Kang

551
00:54:27,597 --> 00:54:30,934
is also doing his best
to climb the mountain in front of him

552
00:54:31,810 --> 00:54:33,853
at the moment.

553
00:54:36,481 --> 00:54:38,274
So I want to try as well.

554
00:54:40,944 --> 00:54:42,237
While imagining that I still have

555
00:54:43,446 --> 00:54:45,991
two strong legs like I used to.

556
00:54:54,833 --> 00:54:56,042
I'm glad

557
00:54:57,877 --> 00:55:00,296
that Kang has you by his side.

558
00:55:55,977 --> 00:55:57,228
-Cha-young.
-Yes!

559
00:56:51,699 --> 00:56:53,493
I know what you taste

560
00:56:54,452 --> 00:56:56,496
and smell like.

561
00:56:57,789 --> 00:56:59,290
I can imagine it.

562
00:57:14,389 --> 00:57:15,306
What's up?

563
00:57:17,392 --> 00:57:19,602
Get up, you fool!

564
00:57:24,566 --> 00:57:26,359
I need to talk to you
when I'm back in Seoul.

565
00:57:28,319 --> 00:57:29,529
About what?

566
00:57:31,072 --> 00:57:33,616
About Grandma, you,

567
00:57:34,576 --> 00:57:36,453
Mom, and me,

568
00:57:37,120 --> 00:57:38,204
as well as

569
00:57:40,457 --> 00:57:43,084
about Kang and his dad.

570
00:58:05,523 --> 00:58:06,733
There you are.

571
00:58:08,985 --> 00:58:10,403
I looked everywhere for you.

572
00:58:13,114 --> 00:58:14,824
When did you wake up?

573
00:58:14,908 --> 00:58:16,367
A little while ago.

574
00:58:17,660 --> 00:58:18,870
I even took a shower.

575
00:58:19,329 --> 00:58:22,165
I had some fresh clothes in the car,
so I got changed too.

576
00:58:24,501 --> 00:58:28,087
Do you remember
that Dr. Lee Jun was here to see you?

577
00:58:30,798 --> 00:58:32,467
I think so.

578
00:58:38,139 --> 00:58:39,724
I feel like

579
00:58:40,308 --> 00:58:42,519
all we've done since coming to Wando
is sleep.

580
00:58:44,979 --> 00:58:46,064
I know.

581
00:58:50,735 --> 00:58:51,653
Aren't you hungry?

582
00:58:54,072 --> 00:58:55,114
I am.

583
00:58:55,782 --> 00:58:57,075
Let's go eat.

584
00:58:57,450 --> 00:59:00,078
I made some food.

585
00:59:03,206 --> 00:59:04,332
Min-seong.

586
00:59:05,083 --> 00:59:09,003
I'm still confused and torn.

587
00:59:10,004 --> 00:59:11,798
But one thing I know for sure

588
00:59:12,257 --> 00:59:15,843
is that I'm tired of doing my best

589
00:59:16,511 --> 00:59:20,223
to push away this woman,

590
00:59:21,391 --> 00:59:24,644
who walked into my life at some point

591
00:59:25,228 --> 00:59:26,938
and has been on my mind ever since.

592
00:59:27,021 --> 00:59:28,690
I won't let you down.

593
00:59:29,857 --> 00:59:32,652
It'll be so delicious.

594
00:59:35,697 --> 00:59:36,698
Let's go.

595
00:59:38,366 --> 00:59:40,785
So I've decided

596
00:59:41,452 --> 00:59:43,121
to just

597
00:59:44,455 --> 00:59:45,498
follow my heart.

598
00:59:47,166 --> 00:59:48,293
I'm sorry.

599
00:59:54,507 --> 00:59:55,717
About Greece...

600
00:59:57,135 --> 00:59:58,678
Can you not go?

601
01:00:05,810 --> 01:00:06,853
And...

602
01:00:09,063 --> 01:00:10,273
can I

603
01:00:14,902 --> 01:00:17,822
love you, Cha-young?

604
01:00:53,524 --> 01:00:55,693
-Come here!
-Wanting to look

605
01:00:55,777 --> 01:00:58,112
like Superman all the time
to the person you like.

606
01:00:59,697 --> 01:01:01,616
If you tell me what you want to eat,

607
01:01:01,699 --> 01:01:02,867
I'll make it for you.

608
01:01:04,952 --> 01:01:06,996
Something that takes
a very long time to make.

609
01:01:09,624 --> 01:01:11,042
Kang and I...

610
01:01:13,795 --> 01:01:15,088
Why must we fight?

611
01:01:16,422 --> 01:01:17,965
I'm just going to think whatever I want

612
01:01:18,966 --> 01:01:21,719
and assume that you came
because you were so worried about me.

613
01:01:22,720 --> 01:01:24,681
Eating delicious food

614
01:01:25,056 --> 01:01:27,225
suddenly made me think of you.

615
01:01:28,810 --> 01:01:30,269
I'm going to

616
01:01:31,771 --> 01:01:33,731
tell you a very long story.

617
01:01:35,858 --> 01:01:37,151
Will you listen?

